        },
        "subject": "LU-3582 test: Make stopall safer for data",
        "message": "LU-3582 test: Make stopall safer for data\n\nCalling stopall can lead to orphaned data in the filesystem.\n\nReorder stopall to unmount the OSTs before the Metadata servers.\nProved an optional \"safe\" argument that will umount without -f\n\nRuntests is adjust to use this new \"safe\" option.\n\nSigned-off-by: Keith Mannthey <keith.mannthey@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I87bcf397b6e83252a0960d6eb8024b5d076c5c18\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
